townsman: Doctor Rizal, thank you for helping our community.
Rizal: It is my duty to serve wherever I am.
josephinebracken: Even in exile, you continue your work.
Rizal: Exile does not mean the end of purpose.
josephinebracken: You have built a school, a clinic, and helped so many.
Rizal: If I cannot serve the nation as a whole, I will serve the people here.
townsman: You have given hope to Dapitan.
Rizal: Hope is the beginning of change.